p.text: We hope you enjoy the game as much as we have enjyed making it.
"Start by doing what's necessary; then do what's possible; and suddenly you are doing the impossible."
You begin the game outside halls. This is the base for the game. From here you can walk or get a taxi into town and begin the great adventure that is a Cardiff night out.
Clubs are the highlight of any night out. In the game we have a variety of clubs to choose from. You'll learn about where things are and what differences each of them offer by playing out game.

A major part of the game is the various fast food outlets that the game offers. From local kebab shops to KFC, our game will take the player on an adventure discovering the options of a post-night scoff.

Finally we have Dragon Taxis. This taxi firm works closely with Cardiff Uni and is the sole taxi company in our game. Give them a call anytime for a safe lift to another location saving you from walking long distances.
But how did we do it?
But don't take it from us, listen to what customers had to say...
Clubs - The Good, the Bad and the Ugly
I don't know if I can handle my drink!
What if I lose my keys?
These problems face every single Fresher
But we are here to help!
Blood alcohol level can rise rapidly when you are pressured to drink.
Drinking is a central part of the game.
Drink too little and your night will not be deemed a success but drink to excess and a trip to A&E is inevitable.
Get the balance right though and you'll succeed in our game.
Our game will showcase Cardiffs clubs in their true light, allowing Freshers to make more informed decisions when choosing where to go on a night out.
"Drink Till You Drop gave me the confidence to explore Cardiff without having to make the fatal error of entering Tiger Tiger and having to pay with real money!" - Alice, English Literature

"I wish I had this last year when I was a Fresher, to be able to learn how to handle your drink in a safe environment has given me the confidence to go out and mee more people!" - Ruth, Accounting and Finance
"I wish my team had thought of this game." - George, Computer Science
Created a detailed map with over 25 rooms and 20 consumables.
